	pageEncoding="UTF-8"%>

<div class="row">
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<div class="recipe-modal-img-container">
			<img src="${pageContext.request.contextPath}/recipes/Shepherds_Pie.jpg" />
		</div>
		<h4>Ingredients</h4>
		<ul class="ingredients">
			<li>1 pound lean ground beef</li>
			<li>1 packet IP chicken a la king</li>
			<li>1 small zucchini, grated or cubed</li>
			<li>1 cup broccoli slaw</li>
			<li>1 green bell or red pepper, chopped</li>
			<li>4-6 green onions, chopped</li>
			<li>1 head cauliflower</li>
			<li>1 Tbsp butter</li>
			<li>salt, pepper, onion and garlic powder to taste</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<h4>Instructions</h4>
		<ol class="instructions">
			<li>preheat oven to 375F
			<li>stir fry beef in large skillet</li>
			<li>while beef is cooking, add cauliflower and 1 cup water to pan and bring to a boil until cauliflower has softened</li>
			<li>add the zucchini, broccoli slaw, bell pepper, and onions to meat and cook until veggies are slightly tender</li>
			<li>add the meat and vegetable mixture to an 8x12 baking dish</li>
			<li>in shaker, add 4 ounces water and 1 package IP a la king mix. Stir chicken a la king into baking dish with the meat and vegetables.</li>
			<li>mash cauliflower with fork until it is the consistency of mashed potatoes. Add 1 small slab of butter, if desired.</li>
			<li>top meat/vegetables with mashed cauliflower.</li>
			<li>bake for 30-40 minutes or until casserole is bubbling and hot and cauliflower is slightly browned.</li>
		</ol>
	</div>
</div>